# Demo Builder — Sanctuary Worship Playback Engine

## What was built

Full-featured Vite + React 18 worship playback app. All audio generated programmatically via Web Audio API (no sample files, no npm audio libs). Build: 215KB JS / 8KB CSS, zero console errors.

**Deployed to:** `../michaelwegter.com/public/demos/audio-software-engineer-needed-for/`

---

## Features implemented (all working)

### Audio Engine (`src/engine/AudioEngine.js`)
- 6-stem OfflineAudioContext synthesis per song: Drums, Bass, Keys, Pads, Click, Guide
- Drum machine: pitch-drop kick (sine 180->40Hz), bandpass filtered noise snare, HPF hihat (closed + open), 8th-note pattern
- Bass: dual-osc (sine + triangle), root-P5-root-root quarter-note walking pattern
- Keys: 3-osc triangle chord (root8va, M3, P5) with LPF + ADSR envelope, beats 1+3
- Pads: 4 detuned sawtoths (-14,-4,+4,+14 cents), LPF 900Hz, tremolo LFO, slow attack/release (most important for worship feel)
- Click: sharp sine transient (1300Hz accent, 900Hz beat), 25ms duration
- Guide: sawtooth with vibrato LFO + bandpass 700Hz (vocal-like), melodic motif per bar
- Per-stem signal chain: AudioBufferSourceNode -> GainNode (vol) -> StereoPannerNode -> GainNode (mute) -> masterGain -> destination
- `source.loop=true`, loop offset via `start(t, offset % buffer.duration)` for sample-accurate seek
- Pause/resume via `pauseOffset` accumulation; seek tears and restarts sources

### Scheduler (`src/engine/Scheduler.js`)
- Chris Wilson 25ms/100ms lookahead scheduler
- Beat callbacks drive Transport beat-flash indicator
- Cue dispatch: compares audioCtx time to cue timestamps, fires once per cue, resets on seek

### Songs (`src/data/songs.js`)
3 songs with full section/cue data:
1. **Endless Grace** (A, 72 BPM) — 9 sections, 200s
2. **Risen King** (G, 132 BPM) — 8 sections, 95s
3. **Holy Ground** (E, 76 BPM) — 8 sections, 190s
ROOT_HZ: A=110, G=98, E=82.4

### Transport (`src/components/Transport.jsx`)
- Play/Pause toggle, Stop, Count-in play button
- Count-in: renders offline click buffer, plays on live context, visual overlay (4->3->2->1->GO countdown)
- Beat flash LED (amber accent on beat 1, dim on beats 2-4)
- Time display (M:SS.d format, turns amber when playing)
- BPM + key + time signature display
- Master volume fader
- Keyboard: Space = play/pause, Escape = stop

### SongSelector (`src/components/SongSelector.jsx`)
- Chip buttons showing title, key, BPM, time sig
- Triggers full stem re-render with progress bar

### SectionNav (`src/components/SectionNav.jsx`)
- Clickable section chips; active chip styled with section color
- A/B loop: [A button sets loop-in at current section start, B] sets loop-out at next section end
- LOOP toggle; loop enforced in AudioEngine rAF tick

### Waveform (`src/components/Waveform.jsx`)
- Canvas fills grid row (ResizeObserver syncs canvas dimensions)
- Background + loop region highlight (amber) + section markers (colored vertical lines + labels)
- Waveform drawn from pads AudioBuffer (or drums fallback); downsampled to canvas width
- Amber playhead line with glow shadow; updates every rAF frame
- Click-to-seek anywhere on canvas
- Loading overlay: spinner + "Generating audio..." + progress bar (per-stem, 0-100%)
- Guide cue overlay: text slides in at cue timestamps, fades after 3.5s

### Mixer (`src/components/Mixer.jsx` + `ChannelStrip.jsx`)
- 6 channel strips: color bar, emoji icon, colored label
- Vertical fader (volume 0-100), pan knob (-100 to +100 = -1.0 to 1.0 StereoPanner)
- M (mute) and S (solo) buttons with danger/solo color states
- Mute + solo interact correctly: muted channels stay quiet even when not soloed; any solo silences all non-soloed channels

### Design (`src/styles/app.css`)
- Grid: 64px Transport | 48px SongSelector | 46px SectionNav | 1fr Waveform | 210px Mixer
- Dark professional palette: bg #0C0C0F, surface hierarchy, amber accent, blue focus
- Google Fonts: Inter + JetBrains Mono
- No em/en dashes in user-visible text (fixed in songs.js cues)

